mean the poorer class and the upper class? Yes, yes. Yes, I should think that - there was always the upper class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5922958 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 Could you tell me what you would call the different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8013821 EK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 Well the people with money and - gentry as you might call it, then the working class were the lower class..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5922958 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 Which class would you say you belonged to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8013821 EK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 Well the lower class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5922958 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 What sort of people belonged to the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8013821 EK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 Well people like ourselves, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15950258\charrsid14430778 you know}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 , like -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5922958 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 What sort of occupations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8013821 EK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 Well the working class people that used to work in the same works as my father and - their families and - all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5922958 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 How about office workers and typists, people like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8013821 EK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 Well they're - well they are the working class more or less aren't they.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5922958 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 You'd include them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8013821 EK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 Include - that's the - working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5922958 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 How about shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8013821 EK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 Well I'd class them all as working class, well they'd say working class, middle class and upper clas
s. Well the upper class are the gentry aren't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5922958 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 Where would you put someone who owned their own shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8013821 EK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 Middle class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5922958 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 Do you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8013821 EK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5922958 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 Were you ever taught to curtsey or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8013821 EK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5922958 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 Was there anyone you called sir or master or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8013821 EK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 Only when we were in - in domestic, used to call them sir and madam but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5922958 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 Not while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8013821 EK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 Not - no, not while - no. We used to call the - the schoolmistress miss or the headmistress madam but apart }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11025434\charrsid14430778 from}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778  that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11025434\charrsid14430778 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 
 no. That's all, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5922958 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8013821 EK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11299755\charrsid14430778 In what way do you mean? Oh no, no.
